X,Y
f: X \times Y \to \mathbb R
s_1 : X\to \mathbb R
s_2 : Y\to \mathbb R
s_1(x_0)=\displaystyle \sup_{y\in Y}|f(x_0,y)|
s_2(y_0)=\displaystyle \sup_{x\in X}|f(x,y_0)|
\displaystyle \sup_{x\in X} s_1(x)=\displaystyle \sup_{y\in Y} s_2(y)
\displaystyle \sup_{x\in X}(\displaystyle \sup_{y\in y}|f(x,y)|) = \displaystyle \sup_{y\in Y}(\displaystyle \sup_{x\in X}|f(x,y)|)
\displaystyle \sup_{(x,y)\in XxY}|f(x,y)|
f
u=\sup\{|f(x,y)|:\langle x,y\rangle\in X\times Y\}
\epsilon>0
\langle x,y\rangle\in X\times Y
|f(x,y)|>u-\epsilon
s_1(x)>u-\epsilon
s_2(y)>u-\epsilon
u-\epsilon<\sup_{x\in X}s_1(x)\le u
u-\epsilon<\sup_{y\in Y}s_2(y)\le u
\epsilon>0
\sup_{x\in X}s_1(x)=\sup_{y\in Y}s_2(y)=u\;.
